{{Dicdef|date=June 2018}}
{{Wiktionary}}
Similar to [[idolatry]] and [[iconodule|iconodulism]], '''epeolatry''' literally means the worship of words. It derives from {{lang|grc|ἔπος}} ({{lang|grc|épos}}), which unlike {{lang|grc|λόγος}} ({{lang|grc|[[Logos|lógos]]}}) more specifically means ''word'' in [[Ancient Greek|Greek]], and was apparently coined in 1860 by [[Oliver Wendell Holmes Sr.]]<ref>{{cite book |last=Holmes |first=Oliver Wendell, Sr. |author-link=Oliver Wendell Holmes Sr. |year=1860 |title=The Professor at the Breakfast Table}}</ref>

