{{Gaza blockade}} The '''Women's Boat to Gaza''' ('''WBG''') was an initiative by the [[Freedom Flotilla Coalition]] in 2016 to challenge the [[Israel]]i [[Blockade of the Gaza Strip (2007-present)|naval blockade]] of the [[Gaza Strip]]. The WBG consisted of an entirely female crew and one ship, ''Zaytouna-Oliva''. It started from [[Barcelona]] on 14 September 2016 and visited [[Ajaccio]], [[Corsica]] and [[Messina]], [[Sicily]] along the way.<ref name="WBG FAQ">{{cite web |title=Frequently Asked Questions |url=https://wbg.freedomflotilla.org/faq |website=Women's Boat to Gaza |publisher=[[Freedom Flotilla Coalition]] |accessdate=24 October 2018}}</ref> On 5 October 2016, the [[Israeli Navy]] intercepted the Women's Boat to Gaza and detained its crew members, who were taken to the Israeli port of [[Ashdod]]. The activists were subsequently deported to their home countries.<ref name="The Telegraph 5 Oct 16">{{cite news |last1=Sanchez |first1=Raf |title=Israeli navy intercepts all-female flotilla protesting against Gaza blockade |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/05/israeli-navy-intercepts-all-female-flotilla-protesting-against-g/ |accessdate=24 October 2018 |publisher=''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'' |date=5 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=No violence as Israel intercepts women’s boat to Gaza |url=http://www.timesofisrael.com/israeli-navy-intercepts-gaza-bound-womens-boat/?fb_comment_id=1228552607218144_1228603150546423 |accessdate=24 October 2018 |publisher=''[[The Times of Israel]]'' |date=5 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Booth |first1=William |last2=Eglash |first2=Ruth |title=Israel sends female naval cadets to stop women's boat headed to Gaza |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/israel-sends-female-naval-cadets-to-stop-womens-boat-headed-to-gaza/2016/10/05/740aecfe-8b13-11e6-8cdc-4fbb1973b506_story.html |accessdate=24 October 2018 |publisher=''[[The Washington Post]]'' |date=5 October 2016}}</ref><ref name="Legal Cases">{{cite web |title=Gaza Freedom Flotillas-Ships, Passengers & Lawsuits Against the Israeli government |url=https://legalcasesagainstisraelattacksoncivilianboatstogaza.wordpress.com/2017/06/03/31-boats-challenge-israeli-naval-blockade-of-gaza/ |website=Legal Cases Against Israeli Attacks on Civilian Boats to Break the Illegal Israeli Blockade of Gaza |accessdate=24 October 2018}}</ref>
==Goals and objectives== The Freedom Flotilla Coalition launched the Women's Boat to Gaza to raise awareness of the role of women in advancing the Palestinian struggle in the Palestinian Territories and diaspora. The Women's Boat to Gaza also supported the goals of the [[Boycott, Divestment and Sanctions]] campaign:
# Ending its [[Israeli-occupied territories|occupation]] and colonization of all Arab lands and dismantling the [[Israeli West Bank barrier|Wall]]; # Recognizing the fundamental rights of the [[Arab citizens of Israel|Arab-Palestinian citizens of Israel]] to full equality; and # Respecting, protecting and promoting the rights of [[Palestinian refugees]] to [[Palestinian right of return|return to their homes and properties]] as stipulated in [[United Nations General Assembly Resolution 194|UN Resolution 194]].<ref name="WBG FAQ" />
==Participants== The Women's Boat to Gaza had a total of 26 participants. The voyage was divided into three legs: Barcelona to Ajaccio, Ajaccio to Messina, and Messina to Gaza. Each leg was crewed by thirteen volunteers with several members alternating at different legs of the voyage.<ref name="Barcelona to Ajaccio">{{cite web |title=Participants on Board: Barcelona to Ajaccio |url=https://wbg.freedomflotilla.org/passengers-barcelona-to-ajaccio |website=Women's Boat to Gaza |publisher=[[Freedom Flotilla Coalition]] |accessdate=24 October 2018}}</ref><ref name="Ajaccio to Messina">{{cite web |title=Participants on Board: Ajaccio to Messina |url=https://wbg.freedomflotilla.org/participants |website=Women's Boat to Gaza |publisher=[[Freedom Flotilla Coalition]] |accessdate=24 October 2018}}</ref><ref name="Messina to Gaza">{{cite web |title=Participants on Board: Messina to Gaza |url=https://wbg.freedomflotilla.org/participants-on-board-messina-to-gaza |website=Women's Boat to Gaza |publisher=[[Freedom Flotilla Coalition]]|accessdate=24 October 2018}}</ref><ref name="Legal Cases" />
